CatDescriptText: Thomas E. Finney, 7525 Upland Street, Republican, 13th Ward, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 7, 1957, pg. 3 with question: "Who is your Ward Chairman? Does he have any power? Does he exert it?" Answer reads: "Yes, I know the ward chairman although I can't pronounce his name. I know him personally.  I don't know about this power because this is a Democratic stronghold.  However, I do know that whenever we want something done, it is done immediately."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Thomas E. Finney standing in front of open car door on Centre Avenue, with Olivet Baptist Church in background
